{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"33ghjrlsel9tgnyaceakqaa","title":"2022-06-30","desc":"","updated":1658630383596,"created":1656554291393,"traitIds":["lessons"],"custom":{},"fname":"lessons.2022.06.30","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"8f0c0cce7cc9342febc5ebae0a25708c","links":[],"anchors":{"class-notes":{"type":"header","text":"Class Notes","value":"class-notes","line":10,"column":0,"depth":2},"称呼-chēng-hu":{"type":"header","text":"称呼 chēng hu","value":"称呼-chēng-hu","line":12,"column":0,"depth":3},"phrases":{"type":"header","text":"Phrases","value":"phrases","line":41,"column":0,"depth":3},"vocabulary":{"type":"header","text":"Vocabulary","value":"vocabulary","line":48,"column":0,"depth":2},"境-jìng---border":{"type":"header","text":"境 jìng - border","value":"境-jìng---border","line":52,"column":0,"depth":3},"附-fù---attach":{"type":"header","text":"附 fù - attach","value":"附-fù---attach","line":63,"column":0,"depth":3},"个子-gè-zi---tall--height":{"type":"header","text":"个子 gè zi - Tall / Height","value":"个子-gè-zi---tall--height","line":71,"column":0,"depth":3}},"children":[],"parent":"8vvjb96x18dhf64wujrrmro","data":{},"schema":{"schemaId":"day","moduleId":"lessons"}},"body":"<h1 id=\"2022-06-30\">2022-06-30<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#2022-06-30\"></a></h1>\n<h2 id=\"class-notes\">Class Notes<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#class-notes\"></a></h2>\n<h3 id=\"称呼-chēng-hu\">称呼 chēng hu<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#称呼-chēng-hu\"></a></h3>\n<p><em>a way to address someone</em></p>\n<p>Two different connotations to the same 词 (cí)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>大爷 dà ye - uncle, endearing term for an older man</li>\n<li>大爷 dà yé - a useless, controlling / demanding old dude</li>\n</ul>\n<p>In ascending order of age, for a male:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>小伙子 xiǎo huǒ zi - lad</li>\n<li>大哥 dà gē - eldest brother</li>\n<li>大爷 dà yé - Uncle</li>\n</ul>\n<p>In ascending order of age, for a female：</p>\n<ul>\n<li>小姑娘 xiǎo gū niang (likely unmarried)</li>\n<li>大姐 (likely married)</li>\n<li>大妈 dà mā - Aunt</li>\n</ul>\n<p>同志 tóng zhì - in old Communist lingo, this meant 'comrade' and was a common way to greet others.  Now, it has become a term for gay (slur? not sure) </p>\n<p>师傅（父） shī fu - very polite way to address someone</p>\n<p>Other common polite terms: </p>\n<ul>\n<li>先生 xiān sheng</li>\n<li>小姐 xiǎo jiě - although, this now has negative connotations </li>\n<li>女士 nǚ shì - lady, this has now replaced 小姐 because it doesn't have the same negative connotations. It used to be strictly reserved for married women.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Name + 培 péi - a parent may use call their kid this (or someone older calling someone younger)</p>\n<h3 id=\"phrases\">Phrases<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#phrases\"></a></h3>\n<p><em>Old Saying:</em></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>人不如新，衣不如旧。rén bù rú xīn，yī bù rú jiù。 - People are not as good as new, clothes are not as good as old.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>你以为你是谁？nǐ yǐ wéi nǐ shì shuí？ - Who do you think you are?</p>\n<h2 id=\"vocabulary\">Vocabulary<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#vocabulary\"></a></h2>\n<p><em>Review:</em></p>\n<h3 id=\"境-jìng---border\">境 jìng - border<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#境-jìng---border\"></a></h3>\n<p>次 Uses: </p>\n<ul>\n<li>环境</li>\n<li>过境</li>\n<li>国境</li>\n<li>出境</li>\n<li>入境 </li>\n<li>境内 jìng nèi - territory</li>\n<li>境外 jìng wài - Overseas</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"附-fù---attach\">附 fù - attach<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#附-fù---attach\"></a></h3>\n<p>附近 fù jìn - neighborhood</p>\n<p>Similar: </p>\n<ul>\n<li>付钱 fù qián</li>\n<li>付款方式 fù kuǎn fāng shì - Payment Methods</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"个子-gè-zi---tall--height\">个子 gè zi - Tall / Height<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#个子-gè-zi---tall--height\"></a></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>我的身高是1米7.</li>\n<li>我个子很高.</li>\n<li>我个子比较矮.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Some sentences:</p>\n<p>主要影响 zhǔ yào yǐng xiǎng - Major impact</p>\n<p>主要 zhǔ yào - main</p>\n<p>别影响我 bié yǐng xiǎng wǒ - Don't disturb me!</p>\n<p>Subj 1 + 对 + Subj 2 + 的主要影响是。。。</p>\n<p>她的孩子考数学考了最后一名。tā de hái zi kǎo shù xué kǎo le zuì hòu yì míng。</p>","noteIndex":{"id":"tP0mD90vo9yAk1VHyoVSk","title":"Journey in 中文","desc":"","updated":1633192679985,"created":1632988446599,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"e1df6c5df8b29a0b6547a656d6502b4e","links":[],"anchors":{},"children":["VGTsTXhrREuYjcjspAW6g","X9i6HckFgvkUQ0jaz25Gj","iUTqRrhiYl7NrwSzGbeTw","H9qDzxUwhOmeT4zlcaKbf","tSyiuG6PVRvuDxGxvYhxA","YXK3064rlQB4yQa8iOpYT","bxcd0mfv90vkw29jhe56k7q","j8d8u7cnd8bukg2fwl4kxno"],"parent":null,"data":{},"body":"\nIn this journal, I document my journey in trying to learn Chinese for the 2nd time.\n\nMost of the notes will be from my language classes. Some notes are also arranged as references, for example with grammar and useful vocabulary. But in an effort to practice writing, I will also try to write some notes in Chinese about my experiences here in Beijing.\n\nThe grammar may be poor and the sentences simple, please bear with me. Starting simple is part of the learning experience; hopefully with time the posts will become more interesting!\n\n谢谢！\n"},"collectionChildren":null,"customHeadContent":null,"config":{"version":5,"dev":{"enablePreviewV2":true},"commands":{"lookup":{"note":{"selectionMode":"extract","confirmVaultOnCreate":false,"leaveTrace":false,"bubbleUpCreateNew":true,"fuzzThreshold":0.2,"vaultSelectionModeOnCreate":"smart"}},"insertNote":{"initialValue":"templates"},"insertNoteLink":{"aliasMode":"none","enableMultiSelect":false},"insertNoteIndex":{"enableMarker":false},"randomNote":{},"copyNoteLink":{"aliasMode":"title"},"templateHierarchy":"template"},"workspace":{"vaults":[{"fsPath":"vault"}],"journal":{"dailyDomain":"daily